cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE

The paper introduces a new architecture for sequence modeling using sparse factorizations of the attention matrix, which is a common technique in machine learning for natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper also introduces a variation on architecture and initialization to train deeper networks, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
